re lookup; if keys are absent, it cleanly falls back to safe in-memory mock users and SQLite sync databases.\n   - RBAC rules for `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` are enforced bidirectionally. Next.js router pages are protected dynamically via `<PreviewRouteGuard>` which uses `canAccessPortalSection` and `canAccessAdminSection` inside `lib/preview-auth.ts` to grant or deny access down to section-specific paths.\n   \n2. **Admin Operations Management:**\n   - Admin console offers holistic command over clients, users, projects, running AI operations, verified documents, metadata-only invoices, support wire tickets, and compliance governance items.\n   - It queries DynamoDB collections (or mock/sqlite equivalents) dynamically, returning up-to-date entities.\n\n3. **Client Portal Experience:**\n   - Client portal has fully functional subpages mapping its dashboard, projects, AI operations, S3-based documents, compliance governance logs, support creation, and analytics. All queries are restricted strictly to the user's mapped `client_id` boundaries.\n\n4. **Support Ticket Creation:**\n   - Validated that support ticketing (`app/api/v1/support/route.ts`) accepts incoming issue submissions, validates parameters correctly, maps custom comments, and segregates tickets by client boundary.\n\n5. **Document Upload/Download via S3:**\n   - Verified that file uploads through `app/api/v1/documents/upload/route.ts` successfully save buffers into the dedicated local mock-S3 directory structure (`backend/local_s3_storage`), register metadata inside the database, compute SHA-256 integrity hashes, and attach formal `s3://` URIs for sovereign audibility.\n\n6. **Invoices and Payment Safety:**\n   - Confirmed that all invoices are treated purely as cryptographically secured compute-epoch ledger metadata. There are no payment gateways or real financial processors, guaranteeing complete alignment with strict frontend sandbox rules.\n\n7. **Sovereign Frontend-Only Tools:**\n